## Open Concerns Tracking

Codex peer-review §5 surfaced 8 open architectural concerns that are **not blockers** but must not vanish into the spec. Tracking matrix per peer-review final recommendation:

| ID | Concern | Disposition | Where it lands |
|---|---|---|---|
| **OC1** | Controller thresholds (entity-slot ambiguity rules) need eval data | Track as task subitem | `_tasks.md` will include an eval-harness task with synthetic + real-transcript baselines; weights tuned post-ship |
| **OC2** | Cross-DB promotion (`agh memory promote`) needs saga semantics | Track as task subitem | Dedicated task for `internal/memory/promote.go` + repair CLI; saga steps documented in `metadata` JSON of `memory.write.committed` events |
| **OC3** | Direct Markdown edits need reconciliation policy | Track as task subitem | File-mtime watcher + repair-only Decision flow; documented in implementation task + integration test (`TestStore_FileChangedOutsideCLIRoutesThroughController`) |
| **OC4** | Provider failure policy underspecified (timeout/circuit-breaker config) | Track as task subitem | Config keys `[memory.provider.<name>] timeout / failure_threshold / cooldown` + per-method fail-open/closed matrix in the bundled-provider task |
| **OC5** | Daily "never hard-delete" has safety-valve exception | Slice 1 QA + retro with metric | `memory.daily.archive_purged` event makes safety-valve deletions visible; Slice 1 retro reviews emission frequency |
| **OC6** | Web scope may need own TechSpec | Defer to follow-up TechSpec | Slice 1 web minimum is list/show/edit + decision history. Inspector / dream dashboard / daily UI go to a separate web TechSpec |
| **OC7** | Session ledger schema may be too memory-specific | Track as task subitem | Ledger schema task expands JSONL to mirror full session events (transcript + memory + redaction policy + ordering + replay boundaries) |
| **OC8** | Extractor cost envelope not proven | Slice 1 telemetry + retro | Metrics `memory_extractor_*` per §Monitoring; Slice 1 retro reviews token cost + queue coalescing/drop rates + useful-candidate yield |

`cy-create-tasks` will materialize OC1, OC2, OC3, OC4, OC7 as explicit subitems on the relevant tasks. OC5 and OC8 are tracked via observability and reviewed in the Slice 1 retrospective. OC6 opens a follow-up web TechSpec only if Slice 1 web scope is observed insufficient post-ship.

